00:11:11,605 --> 00:11:12,954
that appendectomy back in '09,

249
00:11:12,989 --> 00:11:15,373
which led to a
post-op infection.

250
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:17,069
Which led to recurrent
bowel obstruction

251
00:11:17,093 --> 00:11:18,910
and small bowel resection.

252
00:11:18,945 --> 00:11:22,630
Every time I lose intestine...
my dinner plate shrinks.

253
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,883
I just want to break this
cycle once and for all.

254
00:11:24,918 --> 00:11:26,229
And we are gonna
make that happen for you.

255
00:11:26,253 --> 00:11:28,887
This operation is
extremely delicate.

256
00:11:28,922 --> 00:11:30,716
But I am precise and
I have the patience

257
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:33,007
of a western
diamondback rattlesnake.

258
00:11:34,961 --> 00:11:37,001
Rattlesnakes are
patient. Come on, fellas.

259
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:40,047
Okay.

260
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,866
Okay, you cut me open.

261
00:11:41,902 --> 00:11:43,913
Just do your best to
make it the last time.

262
00:11:43,937 --> 00:11:45,820
Best is my only
mode, Mr. Landry.

263
00:11:45,856 --> 00:11:48,622
- See you soon.
- Thank you, guys.

264
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:53,194
Oh, that's a handball!

265
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,165
Huh.

266
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:01,569
I wonder where Molly gets
her scratching habit from.

267
00:12:04,324 --> 00:12:06,708
You see how wound
up my daughter is now?

268
00:12:06,743 --> 00:12:09,960
You should have seen her
before Derek came along.

269
00:12:09,996 --> 00:12:12,880
I'm not sure what
we'd do without him.

270
00:12:12,915 --> 00:12:15,066
Mm. Let's not go there.

271
00:12:22,259 --> 00:12:25,075
Derek has a mass in his chest.

272
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:36,454
Ring the Bell.

273
00:12:36,489 --> 00:12:38,956
Aw, you got a case
of the scurvy, matey.

274
00:12:38,991 --> 00:12:41,159
Let's-let's just not do that.

275
00:12:41,194 --> 00:12:43,077
Ah, where's the Hollywood smile?

276
00:12:43,112 --> 00:12:45,096
I loved the whole schtick.

277
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:47,081
It's not a schtick.

278
00:12:47,134 --> 00:12:49,550
It's medicine, only on TV.

279
00:12:49,586 --> 00:12:51,753
Right.

280
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:53,972
Now if you'll excuse me,

281
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:55,906
I have a gallbladder removal.

282
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,519
Oh, uh, we-we weren't sure if
you were coming back today,

283
00:12:57,543 --> 00:12:59,138
so they moved
that up the schedule

284
00:12:59,162 --> 00:13:00,322
and I covered that for you.

285
00:13:03,116 --> 00:13:05,076
We... You were
off doing your thing.

286
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:08,018
Which is definitely
not a schtick.

287
00:13:13,443 --> 00:13:15,142
Yeah.

288
00:13:15,177 --> 00:13:17,161
Full day.

289
00:13:17,196 --> 00:13:19,063
I got to jet.

290
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:21,833
<i>Hey.</i>

291
00:13:21,868 --> 00:13:24,602
I just got a readmissions
alert in my e-mail.

292
00:13:24,638 --> 00:13:26,615
Why is Dawn Long
back in this hospital?

293
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:30,041
- She's sick.
- Is that supposed to be a joke?

294
00:13:30,076 --> 00:13:33,644
She's been back here five
times since her operation.

295
00:13:33,679 --> 00:13:35,641
Her treatment costs
are beginning to add up.

296
00:13:35,665 --> 00:13:37,999
You're supposed to be making
us money, not costing us.

297
00:13:38,034 --> 00:13:42,020
The woman is comatose.
Why are we not letting her die?

298
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:44,004
We will. Tomorrow.

299
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:47,375
Care to elaborate?

300
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,660
After six months, Dawn
Long's survival statistics

301
00:13:49,695 --> 00:13:52,463
will no longer be
tracked, and our famous

302
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:56,150
Mother of all Surgeries
will have an official survivor.

303
00:13:56,185 --> 00:13:57,952
It's one for the record books.

304
00:13:57,987 --> 00:14:00,872
- And that six month mark...
- Is tomorrow.

305
00:14:02,275 --> 00:14:04,086
She lives through the
night, then all of the publicity

306
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,221
we got from that surgery
will not go to waste.

307
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:08,696
We just need to keep her
breathing until the morning.

308
00:14:08,731 --> 00:14:10,092
And the family is
on board for that?

309
00:14:10,116 --> 00:14:11,916
They will be.

310
00:14:13,703 --> 00:14:15,169
Okay.

311
00:14:15,204 --> 00:14:18,105
One more day, then
end this charade.

312
00:14:21,243 --> 00:14:23,026
Question.

313
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:25,212
Why is she so sick?

314
00:14:25,247 --> 00:14:28,533
She's bedridden, on a vent,
decrease in swallowing function.

315
00:14:28,568 --> 00:14:31,068
All adds up to
pneumonia. Very common.

316
00:14:31,104 --> 00:14:32,419
Are you sure?

317
00:14:33,473 --> 00:14:35,255
It's pneumonia. Trust me.

318
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:48,336
A mass?

319
00:14:48,371 --> 00:14:51,605
- What kind of mass?
- We're not sure yet.

320
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,875
Is there a chance he'll
have to stay overnight?

321
00:14:53,910 --> 00:14:55,437
We've got softball
tomorrow, Dad.

322
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:56,872
I know, honey. Don't worry.

323
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,128
We're just gonna do a biopsy.

324
00:14:58,164 --> 00:14:59,875
It's a quick
procedure in the OR.

325
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,115
But you must have some
idea what the mass is.

326
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:04,051
There's no point in speculating.

327
00:15:06,606 --> 00:15:08,217
Yeah, let's just wait
for the biopsy results

328
00:15:08,241 --> 00:15:10,121
before jumping to
any conclusions.

329
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:13,310
A nurse will prep
you in a few minutes.

330
00:15:15,765 --> 00:15:19,016
I'll be watching
the entire time.

331
00:15:24,174 --> 00:15:25,406
Mom.

332
00:15:25,442 --> 00:15:27,107
What are you hiding?

333
00:15:27,143 --> 00:15:28,804
- Pardon?
- I saw how you stopped

334
00:15:28,828 --> 00:15:30,556
Dr. Hawkins from
talking earlier.

335
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:32,958
You're not fooling me. I know
how you get when you're worried.

336
00:15:32,982 --> 00:15:34,777
My husband has
a mass in his chest.

337
00:15:34,801 --> 00:15:37,167
It's perfectly rational for
me to look for answers.

338
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:39,164
Why don't you take
Josie and grab a bite?

339
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,722
- The biopsy won't take long.
- Josie's coloring. She's fine.

340
00:15:41,758 --> 00:15:44,908
Mom, quit sidelining
me. I'm not 18 anymore.

341
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:47,178
I can handle whatever
it is you're worried about.

342
00:15:47,997 --> 00:15:50,097
I'm not worried about anything.

343
00:15:50,132 --> 00:15:52,933
Everything is gonna be okay.

344
00:15:59,308 --> 00:16:01,392
Retractor.

345
00:16:08,334 --> 00:16:10,029
Molly's nerves are sky high,

346
00:16:10,053 --> 00:16:12,019
and mine are catching up.

347
00:16:12,055 --> 00:16:15,989
We need something
to go smoothly today.

348
00:16:16,042 --> 00:16:17,992
Thank you for
being here, Conrad.

349
00:16:18,027 --> 00:16:21,462
Well, you're family. Of course.

350
00:16:21,497 --> 00:16:24,148
Thank you for taking this, AJ.

351
00:16:24,183 --> 00:16:26,684
Anything for you, Dr. V.

352
00:16:28,054 --> 00:16:31,022
Dissecting down
to the mediastinum.

353
00:16:32,008 --> 00:16:35,025
Scope to me.

354
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:38,562
Passing the scope anterior

355
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:40,047
to the trachea.

356
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:43,484
Identifying my landmarks.

357
00:16:43,519 --> 00:16:44,819
Uh...

358
00:16:48,908 --> 00:16:50,390
All good down there?

359
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:53,639
I'm flush against
the pulmonary artery.

360
00:16:53,663 --> 00:16:55,145
How close is it?

361
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:58,165
Biopsy forceps.

362
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:04,021
Oh, please, don't
nick that artery.

363
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:05,056
He won't.

364
00:17:06,892 --> 00:17:08,372
And...

365
00:17:09,696 --> 00:17:11,528
<i>- fin.</i>
- He didn't.

366
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,995
Let's get this little nugget

367
00:17:16,019 --> 00:17:17,601
to the lab, shall we?

368
00:17:19,973 --> 00:17:22,072
And now we wait for
the pathology report.

369
00:17:23,893 --> 00:17:26,143
I hate this part.

370
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:34,013
Mr. Kim.

371
00:17:34,037 --> 00:17:36,020
Welcome back, Dr. Bell.

372
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:39,039
Can I help you?

373
00:17:39,075 --> 00:17:41,541
I'm just gonna take a
wild guess and assume

374
00:17:41,577 --> 00:17:43,961
you're behind my removal
from the surgical schedule.

375
00:17:45,498 --> 00:17:47,465
That's what you wanted, right?

376
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,134
Why would that be what I wanted?

377
00:17:50,169 --> 00:17:52,753
From what I hear, you've
been AWOL for weeks,

378
00:17:52,789 --> 00:17:54,555
working your second job.

379
00:17:54,591 --> 00:17:57,942
My second job? I'm on a TV
show bringing publicity to Chastain.

380
00:17:57,977 --> 00:18:00,139
And if a surgery has to be
handed off to an alternate

381
00:18:00,163 --> 00:18:02,646
once in a blue moon,
it's a small price

382
00:18:02,681 --> 00:18:05,132
- to keep a top surgeon around.
- Is that what you are?

383
00:18:06,970 --> 00:18:08,435
We all pass our prime,

384
00:18:08,470 --> 00:18:12,389
but we don't all retire
into fame and fortune.

385
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:15,442
Maybe don't look a
gift horse in the mouth.

386
00:18:15,477 --> 00:18:18,412
I see you're having trouble
understanding. I'll simplify.

387
00:18:18,465 --> 00:18:20,998
You lose me, you lose
more than a surgeon.

388
00:18:21,034 --> 00:18:23,434
I know you'd love any reason
to get rid of me, but trust me,

389
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:25,953
you want me cutting
and you want me happy.

390
00:18:25,988 --> 00:18:28,139
Don't be dramatic, Dr. Bell.

391
00:18:28,174 --> 00:18:30,607
I don't want you gone.

392
00:18:30,643 --> 00:18:33,344
I just don't care
if you're here.

393
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:37,865
Feldman.

394
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,301
- Got your page.
- Dr. Bell.

395
00:18:41,336 --> 00:18:43,165
I didn't expect it to
be you. I just asked

396
00:18:43,189 --> 00:18:45,033
for any available
general surgeon.

397
00:18:45,057 --> 00:18:47,458
Well, I'm between
patients at the moment.

398
00:18:47,493 --> 00:18:48,992
What's the problem?

399
00:18:49,028 --> 00:18:51,979
Well, uh... follow me.

400
00:18:52,999 --> 00:18:54,981
Uh...

401
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:00,671
Perirectal abscess.

402
00:19:03,075 --> 00:19:06,143
You expect me to lance
a boil on a patient's ass?

403
00:19:06,178 --> 00:19:08,140
It's too close to the rectal
muscle for me to do it.

404
00:19:08,164 --> 00:19:11,215
Rules dictate a general
surgeon drains it.

405
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:13,751
Sorry.

406
00:19:29,034 --> 00:19:31,652
Good afternoon, Nurse.

407
00:19:31,687 --> 00:19:33,548
Have Pravesh and Nevin
learned anything about Ms. Long?

408
00:19:33,572 --> 00:19:35,056
Uh, not yet.

409
00:19:35,091 --> 00:19:37,074
Her prelim cultures
are negative,

410
00:19:37,109 --> 00:19:39,060
but her BP has hardly improved.

411
00:19:39,095 --> 00:19:40,627
Okay, let's open up the box.

412
00:19:40,662 --> 00:19:43,030
Order fungal markers,
MALDI-TOF, the whole gamut.

413
00:19:43,065 --> 00:19:46,033
Uh, what are we testing for?

414
00:19:46,069 --> 00:19:48,013
Everything. Uh, you know,
I just want to be thorough.

415
00:19:48,037 --> 00:19:50,721
Okay. I'll have Dr. Pravesh
put in those orders.

416
00:19:50,756 --> 00:19:52,673
Nurse...

417
00:19:53,909 --> 00:19:56,910
this case is deeply
personal to me.

418
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:59,379
I brought Dawn
Long into Chastain.

419
00:19:59,414 --> 00:20:00,981
I was her surgeon.

420
00:20:01,017 --> 00:20:02,845
I held her children's
hands through the post-op.

421
00:20:02,869 --> 00:20:06,820
I am gonna be the last
person to leave her funeral.

422
00:20:06,856 --> 00:20:09,323
I put her care entirely
on my shoulders,

423
00:20:09,358 --> 00:20:11,892
and I'm gonna continue
to do so moving forward,

424
00:20:11,927 --> 00:20:13,610
because...

425
00:20:13,646 --> 00:20:15,946
I am her doctor.

426
00:20:15,982 --> 00:20:19,266
Nobody else. Am I
making myself clear?

427
00:20:20,436 --> 00:20:21,764
- Absolutely.
- You're gonna order

428
00:20:21,788 --> 00:20:23,265
that fungal culture
under my name.

429
00:20:23,289 --> 00:20:25,100
And who are you gonna
send the results to?

430
00:20:25,124 --> 00:20:27,108
- You, Dr. Cain.
- Anybody else?

431
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:28,125
No.

432
00:20:28,161 --> 00:20:30,160
Attagirl.

433
00:20:45,144 --> 00:20:47,061
Dr. Bell.

434
00:20:47,096 --> 00:20:48,596
To what do I owe this pleasure?

435
00:20:48,631 --> 00:20:51,031
I heard you're operating
on Bill Landry today.

436
00:20:51,066 --> 00:20:52,816
I am. 5:00 p.m. sharp.

437
00:20:52,851 --> 00:20:54,352
Don't you love punctuality?

438
00:20:56,105 --> 00:20:58,072
- Need an extra hand?
- I do not.

439
00:20:58,107 --> 00:21:00,090
I'm free at 5:00 p.m.

440
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:02,053
Excellent. I've got some
book recommendations.

441
00:21:02,077 --> 00:21:04,962
- I've done a lot
of bowel resections.
- As have I.

442
00:21:04,997 --> 00:21:06,491
AJ, come on, man.
I'm going stir-crazy.

443
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:07,942
My whole schedule's
been cleared for the day.

444
00:21:07,966 --> 00:21:10,000
Right, so you could
be on television.

445
00:21:10,036 --> 00:21:13,153
- Wow. You, too. Okay.
- I'll tell you what.

446
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:15,300
I will keep you in mind
for surgery. All right?

447
00:21:15,324 --> 00:21:17,458
And if I do need you,

448
00:21:17,493 --> 00:21:20,493
- I will make sure to ring the...
- Don't.

449
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:22,369
- Ding, ding, ding,
ding, ding, ding.
- Don't...

450
00:21:41,350 --> 00:21:45,169
Derek has an aggressive
B-cell lymphoma.

451
00:21:54,196 --> 00:21:55,762
I'm so sorry, Kit.

452
00:21:55,798 --> 00:21:57,714
From here on in,

453
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,701
there are two parts
to a patient's life.

454
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:04,004
Before you know you have
cancer and after you know.

455
00:22:04,039 --> 00:22:05,973
Right now, they're
in Derek's room

456
00:22:06,008 --> 00:22:09,125
living in the before.

457
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:12,212
I heard them planning
tomorrow's dinner.

458
00:22:12,248 --> 00:22:14,014
Brainstorming vacations

459
00:22:14,067 --> 00:22:17,117
for after Molly's
school is finished.

460
00:22:17,152 --> 00:22:18,485
But you and I...

461
00:22:18,521 --> 00:22:21,021
We're already
living in the after,

462
00:22:21,074 --> 00:22:23,573
where you don't plan vacations,
where you know everything

463
00:22:23,609 --> 00:22:25,192
is not gonna be okay

464
00:22:25,227 --> 00:22:27,962
for a very long time, if ever.

465
00:22:27,997 --> 00:22:30,197
And we must drag them
into the after with us,

466
00:22:30,232 --> 00:22:33,217
and that is a terrible,
terrible thing to do.

467
00:22:33,252 --> 00:22:35,218
I could tell them for you.

468
00:22:35,254 --> 00:22:37,721
No. No.

469
00:22:37,756 --> 00:22:40,390
This is my family.

470
00:22:40,425 --> 00:22:42,087
They're gonna remember
these words forever,

471
00:22:42,111 --> 00:22:45,745
and they must come from me.

472
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:47,982
Cancer?

473
00:22:48,017 --> 00:22:50,233
Mommy, what's the matter?

474
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:53,703
- Daddy?
- It's all right, honey.

475
00:22:53,739 --> 00:22:55,622
It's okay. Everything's okay.

476
00:22:56,692 --> 00:22:57,758
Kit, can you

477
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:58,842
please have someone

478
00:22:58,878 --> 00:23:00,677
take Josie to the play area?

479
00:23:00,712 --> 00:23:02,095
Of course.

480
00:23:02,131 --> 00:23:04,026
- I don't want to go.
- I know, sweetie.

481
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:07,501
It's just, it's, uh, it's
grown-up time right now.

482
00:23:07,536 --> 00:23:09,536
It's fine.

483
00:23:17,079 --> 00:23:19,946
Oh.

484
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,565
Thank you, honey.

485
00:23:28,290 --> 00:23:30,457
What's next?

486
00:23:32,795 --> 00:23:36,563
The oncologist, Dr. Jones,
will be in to talk to you soon.

487
00:23:36,599 --> 00:23:40,067
He's a specialist in
this type of lymphoma.

488
00:23:40,102 --> 00:23:41,963
What are the chances of
me getting out of this alive?

489
00:23:41,987 --> 00:23:43,988
It's survivable.

490
00:23:45,074 --> 00:23:47,107
How survivable?

491
00:23:49,111 --> 00:23:51,879
Dr. Hawkins.

492
00:23:51,914 --> 00:23:54,247
I have a daughter...

493
00:23:54,283 --> 00:23:56,127
and I have a wife
to think about.

494
00:23:56,151 --> 00:23:57,579
I need to know if we
should start making plans,

495
00:23:57,603 --> 00:24:00,921
so please, just
lay it out for me.

496
00:24:00,956 --> 00:24:02,267
There's still a lot
we don't know.

497
00:24:02,291 --> 00:24:04,925
The chemo is called
R-CHOP, and it is not easy.

498
00:24:04,961 --> 00:24:07,410
It'll make you feel
tired, nauseous.

499
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:09,630
Your white blood
cell counts will drop,

500
00:24:09,665 --> 00:24:10,930
it could cause an infection.

501
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:12,828
But when you make
it through that...

502
00:24:12,852 --> 00:24:15,469
Please. What are my chances?

503
00:24:16,839 --> 00:24:19,122
You have a 50%
